The bug in this program is that it's replacing `total` value on every loop 
iteration, so after the last iteration `total` ends up with the `item.cost`
`item.cost` of the last element. 

To fix it, you should add `total += item.cost;` inside your for-loop to acc
accumulate all costs from items instead of just replacing the total with ea
each cost on every loop iteration.

Fixed Program:
```tundra
val items = [
  { name: "a", cost: 2 },
  { name: "b", cost: 3 },
  { name: "c", cost: 4 }
];

var total = 0;
for (item in items) {
  total += item.cost;
}

print(total);
```
This program now correctly accumulates the `cost` of each `item` and prints
prints out the final sum, which is 9 as per your expected output.
